message.entry: Does not support integer only code generation.
Can be used in single-rate mode inside a triggered subsystem, and with asynchronous signals.
Cannot be used inside a triggered subsystem, and with asynchronous signals.
ufix(1) only when output type is ''smallest unsigned integer'' and ASIC/FPGA is selected in the Hardware Implementation Pane.

ufix(1) when ''enable bit-packed outputs'' is not selected, ''output data type'' is specified as ''smallest unsigned integer'' and ASIC/FPGA is selected in the Hardware Implementation Pane. sfix(N)/ufix(N) when ''enable bit-packed outputs'' is selected, and ASIC/FPGA is selected in the Hardware Implementation Pane; N is the ''number of packed bits'' parameter value.
Input can be ufix(1) for hard decision, and ufix(N) for soft decision; output can be ufix(1) only.
When ASIC/FPGA is selected in the Hardware Implementation Pane, output is ufix(1) for bit outputs, and ufix(ceil(log2(M))) for integer outputs.
ufix(ceil(log2(M))) only at the input for M-ary modulation.
ufix(1) at the input if ''input type'' is set to ''bit''. ufix(ceil(log2(M))) at input if ''input type'' is set to ''integer'' for M-ary modulation.
ufix(1) only at the output when ASIC/FPGA is selected in the Hardware Implementation Pane.

ufix(N) or sfix(N) when ASIC/FPGA is selected in the Hardware Implementation Pane and output data-type is set to either (a) Smallest integer or, (b) Inherit via internal rule and at the same time input is non floating-point.
